==English==

===Pronunciation===
IPA: /dʌst/

===Verb===
'''dost'''
# {{archaic}} the present tense form of [[do]] used with the archaic pronoun [[thou]] (singular [[you]])

====Quotations====
*William Shakespeare, Sonnet 142
:If thou dost seek to have what thou dost hide,
:By self-example mayst thou be denied!
:(= "If you do seek to have what you do hide, by self-example may you be denied!")

